Secondarily, the druid in question DID in fact object to this rough treatment.  <br>
<br>
Thirdly, the offending person was the young cleric Soullight, whom Elipson claims as his son.  The cleric in question is a high elf.  <br>
<br>
Fourthly, I would gladly die to defend any Damsel in Distress, and will do so as the cause presents itself.  <br>
<br>
As to the comment that there is such a thing as evil and good races, I can say with absolute assurance that this is not the case.  I have met honorable Iskar, noble TierDal, and valorous Ogres.  I have also met dishonorable humans, foolhardy Dwarves, and cowardly FierDal.  It is not the race that makes one good or evil, it is in the heart and mind.  One who says otherwise and judged a person by their parentage is not worth the effort of saving.<br>
<br>
In closing, I have met Sephros on several occasions.  He is a dark stain on the face of Norrath, however I bow to his roleplaying prowess. (speaking /ooc, he is a good man, and I had the high honor of presenting my in-game bride to him.  He was suprisingly pleasant out of character, and I respect him as a person.)<br>
<br>
And if you feel that this entire thread is in the wrong place, that such matters are not best addressed here, then I have a strictly /ooc reply.  Too bad.  I will do whatever I can to protect others, most specifically the Ladies, from harm and abuse.  If you met me, you would understand.  The character concept of a Knight is simple enough....1/2 US Marine, 1/2 Boy Scout.  Dont like the way I play the game?  The box says its a RPG, so I do so.  I will play my class and my deity as I see fit, and this is how it is.<br>
<br>
Sir Vuel Truthbringer, FAE, KOR<br>
Quis custodiet ipsos custodes?<br>
